alert.note: Alert for Le Sueur; Rice (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Watch issued May 14 at 12:18AM CDT by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...FLOOD WATCH IN EFFECT THROUGH THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Flash flooding caused by excessive rainfall is possible. * WHERE...A portion of south central Minnesota, including the following counties, Le Sueur and Rice. * WHEN...Until 1 PM this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Excessive runoff may result in flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations. Flooding may occur in poor drainage and urban areas. Low-water crossings may be flooded. Extensive street flooding is possible. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - Moderate to occasional heavy rain will continue through the morning. An additional 1 to 2 inches on top of the 2 to 5 inches that have fallen in the last 24 hours could lead to flooding. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: You should monitor later forecasts and be prepared to take action should Flood Warnings be issued.
